We observe that at this point optimal is 32, but later as i decrease cpu overhead this number may decrease.

NOTE: There was an error in this version that did not allow for the pipelining to work. I do not know why there is a difference in performance. (it has to do with the -cm flag in state change callback) 

Version 4:

Moved to rdma_write and added a send message from the writer so when writing finished it lets the receiver know, instead of waiting for enter.
--- BENCHMARK RESULTS ---
Total data sent: 3.81 MB
Elapsed time:    0.1266 seconds
Throughput:      0.2528 Gbps
-------------------------

Version 5:
Added pipelining and changed the exporting of the map. The exporting was happening every time, now it happens only one. Added a function for initialising everything for the -cm flag.

I observed for some reason the pipelining cannot reach a depth bigger than 8. Still trying to figure that out. Probably a bug.
Till now fastest time 4,3 Gb/s at message size of 16000 and 1000 messages

